commit_message: updated README to reflect glob changes
Fixed some syntax errors and bugs: one missing comma, one indentation issue, and one missing wildcard.
Added the fastp and multiQC portions of the pipeline back to the script.
Updated run_plasmid spades to remove all wildcards, since we're automatically generating those files.
Updated run_fastp to use glob instead of os, which will allow it to use wildcards.
Added the html argument to the correct place.
Deleted a function that I'm no longer using.
Resolved a merge conflict between myself and myself.
I've temporarily commented out argparse so that I can only test the spades function.
Organized pipeline into functions so that I can easily test just the assembly portion.
Added slashes to the plasmidspades argument so that it could find the trimmed fastq files
Commented out the trimming and quality control portions of our pipeline to check whether plasmidspades is running correctly.
Clarified that the input data for our pipeline is a directory of fastq files, not fasta files.

updated args.folderlocation to trimmed_dir

The plasmidspades part of the assembly_pipeline script referenced args.folderlocation, which was an artifact of a previous version. I changed this to trimmed_dir, which is a variable that leads to a directory containing trimmed reads.

We should discuss whether to hardcode the locations of the trimmed data and QC reports or make them arguments. For now, I'm just hardcoding them.
updated readme to describe usage and input files
put multiqc report in correct directory
added multiqc, deleted irrelevant comments from script
Created new directories for files processed by pipeline
Summary of Tools to be used
